    entry_requirements = '<div class="section--l section--narrow section rich-text elevator__target" data-elevator-title="Entry requirements" data-student-type="both" id="entry-requirements"> <div class="section__content"> <p style="font-weight:bold;">Entry requirements</p> <details class="accordion accordion--divided" data-once="webform-details-save" data-student-type="both"><summary class="accordion__toggle" data-once="webform-details-summary-save" id="accordion-admission-criteria"><p style="font-weight:bold;"> Admission criteria </p><span class="button button--small button--icon-only"></span></summary><div class="accordion__content rich-text rich-text--contained"><p>Successful completion of one of the following:</p><ul><li>a recognised bachelor degree or a graduate diploma or masters degree in a related area; or</li><li>a recognised bachelor degree plus an honours degree or a graduate diploma or masters degree in a non-related area.</li></ul><p>Related areas include: public health, health science, primary health care, medicine, social science or health promotion</p><p>Note: Bachelor of Nursing is not an approved degree for this course. Applicants with a degree in this field are encouraged to apply for either the Graduate Diploma of Health Research or Public Health. Applicants with extensive experience in rural and remote practice may be assessed on a case-by-case basis</p><p>Applicants who have completed Charles Darwin University''s Graduate Certificate of Infectious Disease Prevention and Control (UIDPC1) or Graduate Certificate of Epidemiology (UEPID1) are also eligible for entry.</p></div></details><details class="accordion accordion--divided" data-once="webform-details-save" data-student-type="international"><summary class="accordion__toggle" data-once="webform-details-summary-save" id="accordion-international-entry-pathway"><p style="font-weight:bold;"> International entry pathway </p><span class="button button--small button--icon-only"></span></summary><div